  "texts": [
    "Having investigated a range of computational aspects of both consequentialism and deontology, we are now in a position to say something more substantial about their difference and potential combination.",
    "First, it should be concluded that the claim \"deontology is, computationally speaking, less complex than its alternatives\" cannot be given a straightforward answer; and in many cases, it is simply false.",
    "Based on the material discussed in this section, we can outline a more nuanced answer:",
    "Page 57 of 90 105",
    "(1) As argued in Sect. 5.1.1, it is a mistake to view rule-following in legal and liberal contexts as computationally simple."
